# Warken, Luxembourg

Warken (; ) is a town in the commune of Ettelbruck, in central Luxembourg. The village has a population of 1,554 as of 2024 and lies near the Wark River.  Warken is a part of Ettelbruck and is split in five departments: Cité Bourschterbach, Cité Warkdall, Cité Breechen. rue de Welscheid and rue de Buerden.
